oads/2018/06/piscina.png\" alt=\"Piscina\" width=\"100\" height=\"56\" /></a> Piscina[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_106\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"100\"]<a href=\"http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/pulperia/\"><img class=\"wp-image-106 size-full\" title=\"Icono de la pulperia\" src=\"http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/pulperia.png\" alt=\"Pulperia\" width=\"100\" height=\"72\" /></a> Pulpería[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_107\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"100\"]<a href=\"http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/tarjetero/\"><img class=\"wp-image-107 size-full\" title=\"Icono del Tarjetero\" src=\"http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tarjetero.png\" alt=\"Tarjetero\" width=\"100\" height=\"124\" /></a> Tarjetero[/caption]','Recorrido','','publish','closed','open','','recorrido','','','2018-06-13 12:59:35','2018-06-13 12:59:35','',0,'http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(3,1,'2018-06-11 10:40:55','2018-06-11 10:40:55','<h2>Who we are</h2><p>Our website address is: http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp.</p><h2>What personal data we collect and why we collect it</h2><h3>Comments</h3><p>When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor&#8217;s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.</p><p>An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.</p><h3>Media</h3><p>If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.</p><h3>Contact forms</h3><h3>Cookies</h3><p>If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.</p><p>If you have an account and you log in to this site, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.</p><p>When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select &quot;Remember Me&quot;, your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.</p><p>If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.</p><h3>Embedded content from other websites</h3><p>Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.</p><p>These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracing your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.</p><h3>Analytics</h3><h2>Who we share your data with</h2><h2>How long we retain your data</h2><p>If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.</p><p>For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.</p><h2>What rights you have over your data</h2><p>If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.</p><h2>Where we send your data</h2><p>Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.</p><h2>Your contact information</h2><h2>Additional information</h2><h3>How we protect your data</h3><h3>What data breach procedures we have in place</h3><h3>What third parties we receive data from</h3><h3>What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data</h3><h3>Industry regulatory disclosure requirements</h3>','Privacy Policy','','trash','closed','open','','privacy-policy__trashed','','','2018-06-13 10:24:44','2018-06-13 10:24:44','',0,'http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/?page_id=3',0,'page','',0),(33,1,'2018-06-11 10:54:37','2018-06-11 10:54:37','Imagen panoramica de la pulpería','pulperia1','Pulperia','inherit','open','closed','','pulperia1','','','2018-06-13 09:43:13','2018-06-13 09:43:13','',0,'http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/pulperia1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(34,1,'2018-06-11 10:54:53','2018-06-11 10:54:53','{\n    \"modern::header_image\": {\n        \"value\": \"http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/pulperia1.jpg\",\n        \"type\": \"theme_mod\",\n        \"user_id\": 1,\n        \"date_modified_gmt\": \"2018-06-11 10:54:53\"\n    },\n    \"modern::header_image_data\": {\n        \"value\": {\n            \"url\": \"http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/pulperia1.jpg\",\n            \"thumbnail_url\": \"http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/pulperia1.jpg\",\n            \"timestamp\": 1528714485934,\n            \"attachment_id\": 33,\n            \"width\": 1920,\n            \"height\": 1080\n        },\n        \"type\": \"theme_mod\",\n        \"user_id\": 1,\n        \"date_modified_gmt\": \"2018-06-11 10:54:53\"\n    }\n}','','','trash','closed','closed','','55d19aac-19ca-4040-a31d-00c4ae88533e','','','2018-06-11 10:54:53','2018-06-11 10:54:53','',0,'http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/2018/06/11/55d19aac-19ca-4040-a31d-00c4ae88533e/',0,'customize_changeset','',0),(8,1,'2018-06-11 10:43:29','2018-06-11 10:43:29','La Corporación Museo del Salitre (CMS) creada por ex habitantes (y sus descendientes) de las oficinas salitreras, con fecha de asamblea constituyente el 23 de noviembre 1997 y fundada el 11 de Noviembre de 1999 según Decreto Supremo Nº912 del Ministerio de Justicia, con domicilio legal en la ciudad de Iquique, Región de Tarapacá, Chile.\r\nPosee un patrimonio constituido por todos los bienes muebles e inmuebles que forman las Oficinas Salitreras Humberstone y Santa Laura, declaradas Patrimonio de la Humanidad por la UNESCO. Ambas salitreras se encuentran en la Comuna de Pozo Almonte.\r\n\r\nA Junio de 2009 la Institución cuenta con 296 socios inscritos, de los cuales 252 corresponden a socios fundadores y 43 son socios activos que se han incorporado en el transcurso de los últimos años. Cuenta a de mas con promedio de 27 funcionarios que acompañan los esfuerzos de la corporación.\r\n\r\nLa Corporación Museo del salitre es una Institución privada sin fines de lucro (Decreto Nº 912 del ministro de justicia, año 2000) cuya misión es proteger, restaurar y administrar las oficinas Salitreras de Humberstone y Santa Laura, Inscritas en la lista de Sitios de patrimonio Mundial, por UNESCO en 2005.\r\n\r\nFue constituida en 1997 bajo el anhelo de recuperar el patrimonio histórico cultural que significó la vida del obrero pampino, y la producción del \"oro blanco\" que constituyó de forma importante a la economía de Chile.\r\n\r\n¿Quienes somos? Objetivos Misión Visión Nuestros Pampinos Semana del Salitre','Nuestra Institución','','trash','closed','closed','','inicio__trashed','','','2018-06-29 18:14:03','2018-06-29 22:14:03','',0,'http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/?page_id=8',0,'page','',0),(9,1,'2018-06-11 10:43:29','2018-06-11 10:43:29','La Corporación Museo del Salitre (CMS) creada por ex habitantes (y sus descendientes) de las oficinas salitreras, con fecha de asamblea constituyente el 23 de noviembre 1997 y fundada el 11 de Noviembre de 1999 según Decreto Supremo Nº912 del Ministerio de Justicia, con domicilio legal en la ciudad de Iquique, Región de Tarapacá, Chile.\r\n\r\nPosee un patrimonio constituido por todos los bienes muebles e inmuebles que forman las Oficinas Salitreras Humberstone y Santa Laura, declaradas Patrimonio de la Humanidad por la UNESCO. Ambas salitreras se encuentran en la Comuna de Pozo Almonte.\r\n\r\nA Junio de 2009 la Institución cuenta con 296 socios inscritos, de los cuales 252 corresponden a socios fundadores y 43 son socios activos que se han incorporado en el transcurso de los últimos años. Cuenta a de mas con promedio de 27 funcionarios que acompañan los esfuerzos de la corporación.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n	<div class=\"col-md-5\">\r\n		[caption id=\"attachment_156\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"250\"]\r\n		<img src=\"http://www.museodelsalitre.cl/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/nuestra-institucion-1.png\" alt=\"prueba - texto alternativo\" width=\"250\" height=\"201\" class=\"size-full wp-image-156\" /> \r\n		Imagen de la reunión de los socios en el año 2009[/caption]\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"col-md-7\">\r\n		La Corporación Museo del salitre es una Institución privada sin fines de lucro (Decreto Nº 912 del ministro de justicia, año 2000) cuya misión es proteger, restaurar y administrar las oficinas Salitreras de Humberstone y Santa Laura, Inscritas en la lista de Sitios de patrimonio Mundial, por UNESCO en 2005.\r\n\r\n		Fue constituida en 1997 bajo el anhelo de recuperar el patrimonio histórico cultural que significó la vida del obrero pampino, y la producción del “oro blanco” que constituyó de forma importante a la economía de Chile.\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n	\r\n','Historia','','publish','closed','closed','','historia','','','2018-06-29 14:15:46','2018-06-29 18:15:46','',0,'http://museodelsalitre.cl/wp/?page_id=9',0,'page','',0),(10,1,'2018-06-11 10:43:29','2018-06-11 10:43:29','<header class=\"entry-header\">\r\n<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><small>Todas sus opiniones son bienvenidas. Comuniquémonos</small></h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class=\"entry-content\">\r\n<div id=\"wpforms-637\" class=\"wpforms-container wpforms-container-full\"><form id=\"wpforms-form-637\" class=\"wpforms-validate wpforms-form\" action=\"https://www.facedchile.org/wp/cms/hablemos/#wpforms-637\" enctype=\"multipart/form-data\" method=\"post\" novalidate=\"novalidate\" data-formid=\"637\">\r\n<div class=\"wpforms-head-container\">\r\n<div class=\"wpforms-title\">Contacto</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"wpforms-field-container\">\r\n<div id=\"wpforms-637-field_0-container\" class=\"wpforms-field wpforms-field-name\" data-field-id=\"0\">\r\n\r\n<label class=\"wpforms-field-label\" for=\"wpforms-637-field_0\">Su nombre <span class=\"wpforms-required-label\">*</span></label><input id=\"wpforms-637-field_0\" class=\"wpforms-field-medium wpforms-field-required\" name=\"wpforms[fields][0]\" required=\"\" type=\"text\" aria-required=\"true\" />\r\n<div class=\"wpforms-field-description\">Ingrese su nombre</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wpforms-637-field_1-container\" class=\"wpforms-field wpforms-field-email\" data-field-id=\"1\">\r\n\r\n<label class=\"wpforms-field-label\" for=\"wpforms-637-field_1\">Correo electrónico <span class=\"wpforms-required-label\">*</span></label><input id=\"wpforms-637-field_1\" class=\"wpforms-field-medium wpforms-field-required\" name=\